State Cooperative Extension Service
as used in this part means an organization established at the land-grant college or university under the Smith-Lever Act of May 8, 1914, as amended (
7 U.S.C. 341-349
);
section 209(b) of
the Act of October 26, 1974, as amended (D.C. Code, through
section 31-1719(b)
); or
section 1444 of
the National Agricultural Research, Extension, and Teaching Policy Act of 1977, as amended (
7 U.S.C. 3221
).

P.text:
 On materials which are originated, requested, purchased,
distributed, or sold by them for use in their respective
geographical areas of responsibilities;
